  "summary": "neon-terminal ships an on-load reverse shell to an ngrok tunnel",
  "details": "Both entrypoints (cjs/src/index.js and src/index.js) spawn `/bin/bash -i` at top-level module load and pipe the shell's stdio over a TCP socket to `2.tcp.eu.ngrok.io:25852`. Any process that `require()`s or `import`s the package immediately hands an interactive shell to the operator of that ngrok tunnel, giving persistent remote code execution on the installer's machine. The package presents itself as a small ANSI color / TTY helper (name `neon-terminal`, description referring to ANSI colors and terminal output, a codes/paint-style API), but the color-helper surface is cover — the network and child_process code has no relationship to the advertised purpose and fires unconditionally on load in both CJS and ESM entrypoints.",
